Subject: [PATCH] ContainerAwareTrait: default $container to null

`Block::getFieldType` (and a few other callers) construct DataObjectType
classes directly without going through the DI container. Those instances
never get setContainer() called, so the typed `?ContainerInterface
$container;` property stays uninitialized. The first read inside
`prepareField()` triggers PHP's "must not be accessed before
initialization" fatal under strict_types=1.

Initializing the property to null lets uninitialized callers proceed;
downstream code already handles a null container (it's typed nullable
on purpose).

Tracking: report upstream at github.com/open-dxp/data-hub-bundle.
---
diff --git a/src/DependencyInjection/ContainerAwareTrait.php b/src/DependencyInjection/ContainerAwareTrait.php
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/src/DependencyInjection/ContainerAwareTrait.php
+++ b/src/DependencyInjection/ContainerAwareTrait.php
@@ -20,7 +20,7 @@ use Symfony\Component\DependencyInjection\ContainerInterface;

 trait ContainerAwareTrait
 {
-    protected ?ContainerInterface $container;
+    protected ?ContainerInterface $container = null;

     public function setContainer(?ContainerInterface $container): void
     {
